Text.SourceString: You said you were a farmer, right?//<portrait=angry>Humph, that explains the outfit. How cute.
Tch. Out of all the places you could go, why on earth would you move here?
What an eyesore that dumpster is. Ugh…
You know, that one in front of the vineyard.//Oh well. It is what it is.
What an eyesore that dumpster is. Ugh…
You know, that one in front of the vineyard.//Oh well. It is what it is.
<NPCName>Ling</> isn’t my mom. Is that a surprise?//I mean, we look nothing alike!
<NPCName>Ling</> isn’t my mom. Is that a surprise?//I mean, we look nothing alike!
Living right next to a lake isn’t that glamorous, honestly.//It can get really loud.
Yeah, the lake is right there in front of my bedroom window…//It’s nice and <Italic>lively</>, I guess, if you want to look at it that way.
What? I’m kinda busy here…
Ah, excuse me.
Oh, I’m afraid I can’t help you. I need to be going.
*<NPCName>Leah</> is ignoring you*
If you’ll excuse me, I have to take some pictures… I’m on a tight deadline here.
Every time I run out of makeup, I have to order it from Pokyo...so upsetting//<portrait=angry>Ugh… Living here is so complicated.
Every time I run out of makeup, I have to order it from Pokyo...so upsetting//<portrait=angry>Ugh… Living here is so complicated.
I don’t know how much longer I can survive living like this.
Ah, <PlayerName>$player</>… Do we have to talk about that?//I’m not interested in talking about fresh vegetables right now. Some other time?
No offense.
I’m leading a yoga class at the community center tomorrow at 10 am.//I’m so excited!
It’s hard to film on the beach. Always so windy, and the ground is uneven. *sigh*
Please go away.
*<NPCName>Leah</> is ignoring you*
If you’ll excuse me, I have to take some pictures… I’m on a tight deadline here.
I try to spice things up and incorporate meditation into yoga too sometimes.//It gets boring otherwise.
Yes… What’s up?
Ah, yes, yes…
I’m really not in the mood, <PlayerName>$player</>.
My earrings were given to my grandmother by the duchess herself. They’re like a family heirloom.//Oh, you can tell?
You sure like to talk, don’t you?
If you think about it, I literally live inside art. That “mansion” has been around longer than any of us.//It was one of the first landmarks here, you know. That counts as art, right?
Well, I don’t know the whole story.//But <NPCName>Ling</> came here to carry out her study a long time ago, and the “mansion” was the only place for sale. So she bought it.
I’m always on the move. Super active.//I don’t do sitting still in one spot very well.
Dad is a teacher, and guess what he likes. Apples!//Such a cliché.
What are you doing? I need to get going.
Can we do this some other time? I’m not in the mood for chitchatting right now.
*sigh*
Mom took me traveling all over the world when I was younger, but there was always art-dealing or gallery opening galas… Work travel.
It was so dull. But I think Mom’s busy schedule pays off…//<portrait=happy>Mom… She always wears the prettiest things.//In retrospect, I probably should’ve studied art like her.
I’m always on the move.//I get bored just sitting in one spot.

I learned that the right accessory can make or break an outfit.//It’s tricky, because you definitely don’t want to look tacky… Like you’re trying too hard.
You seem to… Umm… Be doing just fine with it.

I hate the smell of coffee. It’s so… I can’t find the right word…//Earthy? Bitter? Musty? Anyway…
Dad loves coffee, though. That’s how he starts every day, with a big cup of hot coffee.//What about you? Are you the same?
Wealth isn’t everything, <PlayerName>$player</>.//It buys you better-tasting wine, softer cashmere gloves, but it really doesn’t buy you happiness.
I have a lot of those. Trust me, I’m far from happy.
I think I’m going to take it easy today.//<portrait=concerned>It’s been a hectic day, and it’s only Monday.
<NPCName>Ling</> has a giant case of creepy dolls in the living room. Super weird. Not a great way to greet company, is it?//If she just kept them in the privacy of her room, that might be okay.
Whatever floats her boat, I guess…
For my carefree, effortless look, I’m wearing light foundation and a touch of lip gloss today.//<portrait=happy>You like?
You can’t get anything good around here.//Not even a decent yoga mat.
Preposterous, right? I know I sound dramatic, but you know it’s true.

Preposterous, right? I know I sound dramatic, but you know it’s true.
For my carefree, effortless look, I’m wearing light foundation and a touch of lip gloss today.//<portrait=happy>You like?
Have you heard about a drilling company opening an office here?
In Starlet Town! What could they possibly want with a small town like this?
<NPCName>Ling</> makes such a big deal over Pufferfish moving here. Gosh!
It’s all she talks about at the dinner table.
Bananas are good for you, right?
Let’s see, what’s a good Spring look? Something flowy, definitely. A nice pastel makeup tone. What else, what else…?//<portrait=angry>Are you eavesdropping on me? Of course. You would.
Is this… Is this your Spring look? How…country.
Ugh, Spring.
Ugh, why are you so close to me? You smell like a farm.
I appreciate that you work hard, <PlayerName>$player</>, but my advice? You can still look after your appearance.
I try to take pictures with daisies in the background. They get a lot of likes.//<portrait=angry>But I won’t take any with that patchy grass. So shabby.
With Fall fashion, it’s all about the layers, <PlayerName>$player</>. A jacket, a scarf, whatever you want. Oh, maybe not whatever <Italic>you</> want, if you know what I mean.
I need to prepare for the Spooky Day Festival. My followers love my posts about it.
Personally, I don’t care about the competition between Starlet and Beluga at the Harvest Festival.//<portrait=normal>But my audience eats it right up. Strange…
I like making Harvest Festival content. It’s one of the few good things about this…town.
Dad used to make me do the pumpkin-smashing game when I was a kid…ugh!//<portrait=happy>I won a couple of times.
<PlayerName>$player</>, you could probably use a cute jacket instead of…whatever that is you’re wearing.
Looks like even the snow can make you look cute.
<NPCName>Ling</> is a bit of an oddball, yeah. But she’s actually okay.
Sometimes, it’s not bad to be an oddball. The world needs more of them.
Ugh… Spring feels so long this year. I’m so ready for Summer.
I’m gonna get the perfect Summer glow this year. I just know it.
Have you checked out the Pufferfish office?
They literally built a mini-golf course. Not bad, in my book.
I wanna challenge you to a game of mini golf sometime.
Well, it gets stuffy inside… I prefer to work outdoors, in nature.//It’s a much prettier backdrop.
I don’t know why else. I just like it, I guess… Why does it matter?
The whole island is gathering at the beach tomorrow to pick up trash.
Yes… Trash.
<NPCName>Ling</> is a bit of an oddball, yeah.//But she’s actually okay.
Sometimes, it’s not bad to be an oddball. The world needs more of them.
I honestly think Fall is the best time to vlog at the beach.//It’s way less crowded.
And the weather isn’t too hot.
I honestly think Fall is the best time to vlog at the beach.//It’s way less crowded.
And the weather isn’t too hot.
It’s almost the first weekend of Fall already.//All my mutuals are going to be posting pumpkin pictures soon.
Oh gosh! Next week will be way too late. I need to find a pumpkin before Saturday.
Are you going to have a booth at the Mooncake Festival this year?
Can I take a picture of it? People love country festivals.
I spent two hours on my hair today, and the wind just blew all my hard work away.
Ugh… So annoying.
I spent two hours on my hair today, and the wind just blew all my hard work away.
Ugh… So annoying.
Your boots are so thick. They look super cozy, by the way… Are they designer?
I have to get myself a pair. So country… But I don’t know where I’d wear them.
I haven’t gotten anything for the gift-giving on Sunday. Hmm…
I forgot to get gifts for the twins. Maybe I should just give them to them tomorrow.
The Coral Inn twins, of course. It’s their birthday today.
Yoga’s good for the soul, <PlayerName>$player</>. Haven’t you heard?
You should do it more.
Can’t you see it raining?
I really shouldn’t be out in the rain for too long.
Rain really makes you lazy, doesn’t it? Look at me!//I didn’t even bother putting on decent makeup today!
I can’t wait until it stops. I’m just not the sit-around-doing-nothing type of girl, you know.
I really shouldn’t be out in the rain for too long.
It’s the perfect weather for self-reflective meditation.
Have you ever been afraid your house might be destroyed by a storm?
I forgot my umbrella. Argh…
I hope it stops storming tomorrow. It’s so boring staying inside all day.
Rain really makes you lazy, doesn’t it? Look at me!//I didn’t even bother putting on decent makeup today!
*<NPCName>Leah</> is ignoring you*
Keep your body moving during Winter, <PlayerName>$player</>. It helps keep you warm.
I could use some sun right about now.
I can’t walk in all this snow…
The snow is going to ruin my shoes.
Do I look okay today?
Remember to moisturize after washing your hands. You don’t want chapped hands.
Please don’t touch anything.
I’m having one of those days when a butter croissant is the tastiest thing in the world.
I could eat ten of those. I probably shouldn’t, though.

I could eat ten of those. I probably shouldn’t, though.
The ceramic plates in this house are designer. We have to be extra careful with them.
They belong in a glass cabinet, not in the sink all covered in grease and stew.
This one time, I made a video in the forest, and when I reviewed the footage, I saw I’d caught a slithering shadow.
At first I thought it was a monster, but it turned out to be <NPCName>Taco</>… What a relief!
I think I’d like to adopt a cat and a dog someday.
And then dress them up in couture.//Doesn’t that sound fun?
I don’t like wearing my hair down. It always seems to get in the way.
People think it must be so great living right next to a park, but to be honest, it gets very noisy on the weekends.
You need to join my yoga class sometime.//<portrait=happy>It’ll be fun!
We need to spice things up a bit around here. It looks so dull and one-dimensional.
I’m posting my health checkup video as soon as I get home.
You look a bit under the weather.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe cut back a little on the farming.
I don’t know… You just seem tired, that’s all.
